-- Berkshire’s Gen Re Names Tooker President, Replacing Cholnoky
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2013-09-03T12:28:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-03/berkshire-s-gen-re-names-tooker-president-replacing-cholnoky.html
General Reinsurance Corp., the
reinsurer owned by  Warren Buffett ’s Berkshire Hathaway Inc.,
named Morris Tooker as president.  Tooker will replace John Cholnoky, who is retiring as
president in the first quarter of next year, and will be
responsible for direct property-casualty coverage worldwide, the
Stamford, Connecticut-based reinsurer said today in a statement
distribute by Business Wire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
